==English==

===Etymology===
From the [[Persian]] words {{FAchar|&#1662;&#1575;&#1610;&#1580;&#1575;&#1605;&#1607;}} ''pɑ jɑma'' meaning ''leg garment'' via [[Urdu]]/[[Hindi]] word ''pajama''.

===Noun===
'''pyjamas''' ''plural''
# [[Clothes]] [pa=leg; jama=shirt] for wearing to bed and sleeping in, usually consisting of a loose-fitting trousers but not shirt. A wrong interpretation of pajama in the western world associates a shirt also. As per definition the shirt associated with a pajama is called "kurta" which has not got a western recognition yet.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[pajamas]] (''US'')

====Derived terms====
*[[cat's pyjamas|cat’s pyjamas]]

